message.content:
A bottle is a container used to hold liquids or powders. 
It is typically made of glass, plastic, or metal materials. 
Bottles can come in a variety of sizes, shapes, and colors. 
They can be transparent or opaque, smooth or textured. 
Bottles often have a narrow neck and a wider body. 
They are commonly used for storing beverages, medications, and beauty products. 
Bottles can be found in homes, restaurants, stores, and factories.
